body:
Discussed offline. I think it makes sense to me now. So the timeline would be sth. like:

```
t0: cleanup happened, lastCleanMs recorded;

t1: rebalance happend, store flushed;

t2: cleanup happend again, now > lastCleanMs + cleanTimeMs;
```

Before this patch, we are looking at `t2 - t0`, whereas in this patch we are looking at `t2 - t1`: it guarantees to give use the configured delay time after the rebalance no matter when the last cleanup function was triggered.
